SUMMARY:MONTREAL: Plural Contemporary Art Fair + more   ( our 25th group trip! )
DESCRIPTION:TORONTO ARTS & CULTURE\nThis trip is in 2 months. PLEASE read everything over FIRST!!\n\nTo celebrate our **25th long weekend culture trip**--we return to Montreal...for 4 days. CULTURE CULTURE CULTURE\n\n## Details:\n\n***After an 5-month break\, we will return to Montreal in Spring 2026!!***\n\nOur 25th Group trip (2-3 trips each year since 2016).\n\nAND\, we will return to *PLURAL Contemporary Art Fair*--***-for the 8th time!***\n\nCheck your calendars. All DETAILS are below.\n\n***(Note--this trip is filling up)***\n\n**PLEASE READ** **EVERYTHING** over before signing on--everything you need to know is here. I'll try to make it work--but this trip is always in high demand.\n\n**There is a Non-Refundable fee to join us. Please Email me before signing up. All details are below. $150 per person.**\n\n[https://www.plural.art/en](https://www.plural.art/en)\n\nCan you join us for a mid-April/Spring 2026 long weekend! We have the best time in Montreal!\n\nSomething to look forward to--as Toronto winter approaches. We normally post these trips 4-6 months in advance. This trip is in just 4 months.\n\n--Each trip is unique\, very organized\, individual\, and never to be repeated! For the culturally curious! Art/Food enthusiast. Explorers!\n\nWe can work off a group size of 15 people.\n\n**VERY IMPORTANT**: Please read all the information before signing up to this trip\, as there is a **NON-refundable fee** involved upfront.\n\nCheck your schedules and calendars--and then double check them.\n\n\\*\\*\\*Please do not sign up for the trip until you've emailed me. Very important.\n\nThese are very social trips--we are 'explorers'. Montreal treats us very well. We generally walk everywhere (thousands of steps!)\n\n**We will return to Plural Contemporary Art Fair for the *8th time*.**\n\n[https://www.plural.art/en](https://www.plural.art/en)\n\n**4 nights (Wednesday\, Thursday\, Friday\, Saturday--returning home on Sunday)**\n\n**Plural** celebrates the best of contemporary art in Canada. Created *by* and *for* the galleries\, the fair presents and brings together the plurality of voices and works in contemporary art from across the country. It elevates art market practices through a rigorous selection of galleries presenting thoughtfully chosen artists and artworks\; and through accessible programming that addresses current issues and questions in the field of art.\n\n**Plural's 19th edition** will be held from April 10-12th at the Port of Montreal’s Grand Quay. (Old Montreal). Just a fabulous space/btw. Old warehouse.\n\nIf you are familiar with Art Toronto and The Artist Project\, then you have an idea about Papier Fair. **This is Quebec's most important Art Fair. 50 booths+**\n\n**Also\, on the this trip**\, we will visit OTHER larger Montreal galleries and explore various smaller galleries\, food\, public art\, and architecture. We will meet artists\, curators\, and directors--with private tours. PLUS more.\n\n--We spend most of **ONE** day at the Fair\, then the other time exploring Montreal's vibrant culture scene. After 20+ past trips\, we are so fortunate to have many Montreal culture/gallery friends--they look forward to us/and we to them.\n\nOur full schedule of events is not finalized until late March 2026\, but I keep you posted along the way (every month). **We meet as a group** before the trip in Toronto--mid/late March. TBD\n\nSpecial surprises always await us in Montreal!\n\n***Here is what you need to know to make a decision:***\n\n1. **I will** provide 3 1/2 days of cultural programming **on the ground**. Wednesday night\, all day Thursday\, all day Friday and Saturday. You return home on Sunday at your own time.\n2. **You are** responsible for your own travel\, accommodation\, insurance and other costs you will incur. In the past\, members have travelled either by air\, VIA\, drive\, Bus. They have stayed in hotels (points)\, Airbnb\, Bed & Breakfast\, Hostel\, or with friends.\n\nBy planning ahead\, you can get the best rates etc. VIA and accommodations.\n\nThere is no "wrong" place to stay in Montreal\, but ideally you want to be about 1km/20 mins **walk** from St. Catherine St/Place des Arts.\n\n3\\. These are full trips\\\, with very little "free\\-time"\\. We are on the go\\.\n4\\. On the Saturday night\\\, we have a "full Group" restaurant dinner\\. About $125\\-$150 per person range\\. This is the only formal meal event I organize\\\, although other meals fall into place while there\\.\n5\\. You would need to be in Montreal and ready to go by about 6pm on Wednesday April 8th\\\, and you return home on your own time of choosing on Sunday April 13th\\.\n6\\. Can you attend\\\, please be sure\\.\\.\\.\n\n**There is a non-refundable fee to participate in this trip\, and you MUST connect with me before signing up on Meetup at:**\n\ntorontoisculture@gmail.com\n\nThe non-refundable fee is **$150 per person** payable within 2 days of signing up on Meetup.\n\n7\\. For your budgeting\\\, **other** gallery/event "entry" costs may total $150 maximum over the weekend.\n8\\. By planning ahead\\\, you can get the best rates on travel and accommodations\\. **Be proactive. By doing so\, this covers your non-refundable fee. I travel by VIA\, and stay at Airbnb.**\n9\\. These are NOT expensive trips\\-\\-but they are very rewarding\\! Much of what we do while there is FREE\\.\n\nAny questions?\n\ntorontoisculture@gmail.com\n\nGreg
